source: hand-authored (issue #370 design — sidecar provenance, no live capture)
capture_date: 2026-07-03 (updated 2026-07-04 for #401 pageInfo hardening)
shape: raw `gh api graphql` reviewThreads response (pre-transform) — since #401
  the leaf owns its own jq merge/normalize pipeline (no `--jq` passed to gh),
  so this fixture must match the RAW GraphQL shape including the REQUIRED
  pageInfo{hasNextPage,endCursor} at both the reviewThreads level and each
  thread's comments level. The #401 hardening rejects any response missing
  those required paths (fail-closed on malformed/incomplete GraphQL data),
  which mirrors what a real gh api graphql response always carries.
notes: one unresolved thread + one resolved thread, exercising both branches
  of the resolved boolean. Both threads' comments fit in one page
  (hasNextPage=false), so the leaf's comment-level walk is not exercised
  by this fixture — the runner's _run_review_threads_completeness_assert
  drives review-threads-nested-p{1,2}.json for the nested-comment path.
